The paper discusses the use of millimeter wave frequencies for communication in cellular networks, which falls under the category of networked and internet-connected systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of highly directional antennas and channel models, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses control plane procedures and system parameters, which are relevant to systems and control (cs.SY) and augmented reality (cs.AR).
